commit.message: Zookeeper dependency upgrade.
Updated the Jackson dependency to the latest Jackson.
[fix] Fix a minor unsent-messages bookkeeping issue that was causing a test to fail on windows. Also stress the batching code even more.
[maven-release-plugin] prepare for next development iteration
[maven-release-plugin] prepare release 0.7.9
[fix] Unset count was incorrectly spiking when a downstream node would drop out of the cluster.
[maven-release-plugin] prepare for next development iteration
[maven-release-plugin] prepare release 0.7.8

[fix] Since the batching code the TcpServer wasn't being shut down correctly after a node dropped out. This was already addressed in the trunk. It's now working here also. This also fixes the potential miscount on "messages-unsent" when a send fails in batch mode.
[maven-release-plugin] prepare for next development iteration
[maven-release-plugin] prepare release 0.7.7
[fix] When batching messages, if the first message in a batch is bigger than the mtu, then it wasn't being sent until the next message comes in (or the message timeout). It now sends it immediately.
[fix] There was a slight chance that if the cluster manager failed, then worked, then failed in a short period of time, then a pre-instantiation state change might be missed.
[fix:windows] The Local Cluster manager didn't work on windows since it used the file system line separator in the zookeeper directory structor.
[fix:test] These changes address test stability on underperforming platforms.
The last output cycle time is now represented as a Gage in the monitoring.
[cosmetic] Fix spelling in a javadoc comment.
[fix:test] THESE CHANGES ARE ALREADY INCORPORATED IN THE TRUNK. Address test stability. This correctly resets the state in between subsequent test runs removing any accidental order dependencies.
Refactored the output executor functionality so that it's easy to inherit from and modify.

Added testing and comments and some minor changes for the new batching code. Also made the bytes-sent and bytes-received metrics a Histogram rather than a simple counter.
Added the ability to delay batching to bundle messages into larger packets. Also determined the size of what to send by automatically determining the MTU from the NetworkInterface.

Merge pull request #77 from jimfcarroll/kryo-by-default
Kryo by default
The MpConainer now handles the passivating of Mps when the node's keyspace responsibility changes.
[fix] setting the pending message guage was incorrect.
Better refine the testing for the DefaultDempsyExecutor to verify the exact behavior of the overflow of limited tasks.
This will expose the incoming and outgoing queue depths as a metric in the StatsCollector.

It's no longer possible to get a collision if failFast is false (block is true). It used to be that on the rare occation where eviction was in the process of taking place, and a message came in for the Mp, it could end up marked as a collision. Now it will block until a new one can be created.
Added the ability to get additional metrics throught the MetricGetters for testing.
Use Kryo for the default serialization.
Fix BlockingQueue transport test failures - more.
Fix BlockingQueue transport test failures.
The Passthrough transport now handles the StatsCollector correctly.
Update BlockingQueue transport to use the StatsCollector correctly.
Modify a few tests to check for the condition fixed in the previous commit to avoid it happening again.
[fix] Mistakenly changed the default behavior of the RunInVm class. It's put back now.
Last update was incorrect. This will change the default TcpTransport setting for failfast so that it doesn't actually 'fail fast.'
Change the default TcpTransport setting for failfast so that it doesn't actually 'fail fast.'
Allow the TestUtils.waitForClustersToBeInitialized to also wait for Dempsy to be started.
remove the System.out calls from the TcpTransportTest but set the log level to INFO
remove the use of the @Inject annotation.
Remove System.out calls from the Config tests.
loosen the test requirement for the sending overflow queue since it fails on busy machines.
Add a few more tests for the sending functionality.
Cleaned up TestDempsy a bit.

Added decoupling of workers and sending in the TcpSender. This a small refactor of the interface. Also provides for a watcher that watches for a socket timeout and kills a writing socket if it's hung.
Made RunAppInVm usable from other integration tests rather than only from the command line.
Added a test utility. Cleaned up an unused parameter on another one.
[fix] 'stop' wasn't being called on the executor correctly.
WIP
Added a test for eviction when passivation throws an exception.
Tighten up eviction logic. Prevent a passivate exception from preventing the Mp from being removed from the container.
Tighten up the logic around dispatching messages to the Mp.
Change the default TcpTransport failfast/block during message processing strategy to be 'failfast.' Allow for a better way to configure it than supplying an OverflowHandler.
[cosmetic] Added a comment to the TcpReceiver to clarify how the existence of an OverflowHandler is related to the 'failfast' option.

[fix] A message comming in for an Mp that's currently being evicted can cause that Mp to permanantly hold up worker threads when more messages come in for it. This is now fixed. Also added a metric to monitor for message collisions at the same Mp.
Finding an Mp in the container no longer locks the entire container.
change the log level from ERROR to INFO for log messages when the destination for a message cannot be found.
[fix] Logic was incorrect when determining whether or not a node handles a particular key in the DecentralizedRoutingStratgey.Inbound. Need to handle the negative result of a mod.
kryo serialization can support UIUD now. Also added a test for pre-instantiation failure.
make the multi-threaded serialization test a little less intense.
[fix] Add the serializer application context to the new executor test.

Merge pull request #72 from jimfcarroll/receiver-worker-decouple
Fix tcp bottleneck caused by the fact that the message reading and messa...

Fix tcp bottleneck caused by the fact that the message reading and message handling were done sequentially. Now there is a set of worker threads that handle messages and the read loop is much tighter.

Merge pull request #35 from jimfcarroll/application-info-access
Application info access.
This adds an "Application" level of access to the MpCluster manager. That is, the MpCluster manager now has access at 3 tiers: 1) Slot, 2) Cluster, 3) Application. This is to support dynamic application topology changes by providing Dempsy a place to watch for clusters coming and going.
